Princeton_Recap update_ids array includes different numbers

comments.body:
After searching in the file for these numbers I found out that these are coming from the 876$p 
`tag='876'><subfield code='0'>1254369</subfield><subfield code='3'>Bd.10</subfield><subfield code='a'>5874243</subfield><subfield code='h'></subfield><subfield code='j'></subfield><subfield code='p'>32101074958529</subfield><subfield code='t'>1</subfield><subfield code='x'>Shared</subfield><subfield code='z'>PA</subfield></datafield>`

I think it's more useful to have the barcodes (the 876p values) stored in the dump instead of the bib IDs, since many barcodes can exist under one bib. So knowing which items were sent is more useful than bib IDs.
